1. HTML stands for hyper text markup language . 

2. A language used to describe something is called as a markup language . 

3. HTML constitutes of elements which is used to describe different types of content . 

4. Element is made up of 3 parts :
a> opening tag 
b> content 
c> closing tag 

5. If an element has no closing tag it is omitted . 


A padding is an empty space that is present inside an element . 
A margin is an empty space around the element . 
Fill area is the area that gets filled with the background color .

When margins occupy the same space , they just coalesce to  form a single common padding . This is called as coalescing space . 